WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:14.260 --> 00:00:15.476
Thank y'all!
谢谢大家!

2
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:17.716
This is going to be a motivational speech.
接下来的演讲将会非常鼓舞人心,

3
00:00:17.740 --> 00:00:18.940
Because --
因为 ——

4
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:26.500
imagine my motivation standing between this strong, healthy crowd ...
想象一下，我的动力正处在 这个强健的观众群

5
00:00:27.420 --> 00:00:28.796
and lunch.
和午餐之间。

6
00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:30.356
(Laughter)
（笑声）

7
00:00:30.380 --> 00:00:31.580
So ...
所以......

8
00:00:33.460 --> 00:00:35.596
I'm @Falkvinge on Twitter.
我推特账号是@Falkvinge，

9
00:00:35.620 --> 00:00:40.076
Feel free to quote me if I say something memorable, stupid, funny, whatever.
若我在演讲中说了些有意义的、愚蠢的、 或有趣的内容，不论是什么请放心引用。

10
00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:41.836
I love seeing my name on Twitter.
我喜爱看到我的名字出现在推特上。

11
00:00:41.860 --> 00:00:43.076
So ...
所以，

12
00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:44.540
Hi! I'm Rick.
嘿，我是瑞克，

13
00:00:45.340 --> 00:00:46.540
I'm a politician.
我是一个政客。

14
00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:48.460
I'm sorry.
非常抱歉。

15
00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:54.436
How many in here have heard of the Swedish Pirate Party before?
你们中有多少之前听说过 瑞典海盗党？

16
00:00:54.460 --> 00:00:55.740
Let's see a show of hands.
让我们看看有多少人举手。

17
00:00:57.060 --> 00:00:58.676
OK, that's practically everybody.
好吧，基本上每个人 都有听说过，

18
00:00:58.700 --> 00:01:01.316
Probably due to the fact that we are Sweden's neighbor.
也许是因为我们是 瑞典的邻居。

19
00:01:01.340 --> 00:01:04.916
I frequently ask how many have heard of any other political party
我常常问人们是否听说过 任何其它党派，

20
00:01:04.940 --> 00:01:07.556
and there's always just scattered hands in the audience
在观众中只是零零星星几个人。

21
00:01:07.580 --> 00:01:11.036
compared to this first question which is one-half to two-thirds.
相比较，刚刚的第一个问题 有一半到三分之二的人举手。

22
00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:13.756
This is actually the first time ever that does not match.
真的挺不一样的。

23
00:01:13.780 --> 00:01:15.180
It was practically everybody.
几乎所有人都举手了。

24
00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:19.716
So, for those who haven't heard of us:
那么，对于那些没有听说过我们的，

25
00:01:19.740 --> 00:01:22.100
well, the Pirate Party, we love the net.
我们海盗党，我们喜爱网络。

26
00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:27.180
We love copying and sharing, and we love civil liberties.
我们喜爱拷贝和分享 而且我们热爱公民自由。

27
00:01:28.300 --> 00:01:30.780
For that, some people call us pirates.
因为那些原因， 有些人把我们叫做海盗（盗版）。

28
00:01:31.740 --> 00:01:34.716
Probably in an attempt to make us bow our heads and feel shame.
也许是想有意羞辱我们， 让我们站不直腰板。

29
00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:36.076
That didn't work very well.
但对我们却没有起到什么作用。

30
00:01:36.100 --> 00:01:38.356
We decided to stand tall about it instead.
我们决定站直腰板，

31
00:01:38.380 --> 00:01:42.076
And so in 2006, I founded a new political party.
所以，在2006年 我创立了一个新的政党，

32
00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:44.356
I led it for its first five years.
开始的五年，我引领着这个党。

33
00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:47.756
And the European elections, the last European elections,
在最近几次欧洲选举中，

34
00:01:47.780 --> 00:01:50.196
we became the largest party
我们变成了最大的

35
00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:53.660
and the most coveted youth demographic, sub-30.
和最受30岁以下的 年轻人欢迎的党派。

36
00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:56.756
And what's interesting is we did that
我们用了不到竞争者1%的预算

37
00:01:56.780 --> 00:02:01.220
on less than one percent of the competition's budget.
做出了这个成绩。

38
00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:06.340
We had a campaign budget total of 50,000 euros.
我们的竞选总预算是5万欧元。

39
00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:10.620
They had six million between them -- and we beat them.
他们有6百万欧元， 我们战胜了他们。

40
00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:19.100
That gave us a cost efficiency advantage of over two orders of magnitude.
我们的成本效率优势 是其他党派的两个数量级。

41
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:24.420
And I'm gonna share the secret recipe of how we did that.
现在我将要分享 我们的成功秘笈。

42
00:02:27.260 --> 00:02:30.060
We developed swarm methodologies.
我们发展了集群智能方法。

43
00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:36.220
And they can be applied to any business or social cause.
它们可以应用于任何商业或 社会问题上。

44
00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:38.916
Well, almost any --
好吧，几乎是“任何”，

45
00:02:38.940 --> 00:02:40.676
there's a small asterisk by the end,
“任何”上打着一个小星号，

46
00:02:40.700 --> 00:02:42.836
and I'll get to that in just a minute.
我一会儿将给予解释。

47
00:02:42.860 --> 00:02:44.556
But applying these --
但是应用这些－－

48
00:02:44.580 --> 00:02:48.516
and we've done this dozens of times, we know that this works.
我们实践了这个方法许多次， 它是非常有效的。

49
00:02:48.540 --> 00:02:51.236
We've put two people in the European Parliament,
我们的两位成员已入驻欧洲议会，

50
00:02:51.260 --> 00:02:54.156
we have 45 people in various German state parliaments,
我党在德国各个州立议会中 已有45名议员，

51
00:02:54.180 --> 00:02:57.716
we're in the Icelandic parliament, the Czech senate,
我们在冰岛议会，捷克参议院，

52
00:02:57.740 --> 00:02:59.716
many, many, many more, local councils --
在很多，很多地方议会 生根发芽。

53
00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:02.396
and, as said, we've spread to 70 countries.
我党已经扩展到了70个国家。

54
00:03:02.420 --> 00:03:04.476
And that's not bad for a political movement
对一个成立不到十年的政治运动来说，

55
00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:06.540
that hasn't even been around for a decade.
这个成绩不算坏。

56
00:03:09.140 --> 00:03:11.460
So today we're going to talk a bit about --
所以今天，我们要讨论的是：

57
00:03:13.180 --> 00:03:17.220
how people are motivated to be part of change,
人们是如何被鼓舞参与变革，

58
00:03:18.140 --> 00:03:20.420
to be part of something bigger than themselves.
投身于大于自身的运动中。

59
00:03:21.580 --> 00:03:25.676
And how you can channel this into an organization
以及你该如何把这种精神 引导到你的组织中，

60
00:03:25.700 --> 00:03:32.460
that harnesses this great power of wanting to make the world a better place.
善用“让世界变得更美好” 这思想的巨大力量。

61
00:03:33.740 --> 00:03:37.700
And in the end, come out a little on the better.
最后，不断得出更好的结果。

62
00:03:39.940 --> 00:03:44.396
When I speak to businesspeople, I frequently make them very upset
当我和商人们交谈时， 当我提出与其相异的观点，

63
00:03:44.420 --> 00:03:46.276
when I contradict them
他们会特别生气。

64
00:03:46.300 --> 00:03:52.460
and say that no, your employees are not your most valuable asset.
我告诉他们说，不，你的雇员 不是你最宝贵的资产。

65
00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:56.916
Your most valuable asset is the thousands of people
你最宝贵的资产 是成千上万的

66
00:03:56.940 --> 00:03:59.556
who want to work for you for free.
想为你免费工作的人。

67
00:03:59.580 --> 00:04:00.980
And you don't let them.
你还不让他们。

68
00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:04.340
They get very upset about that.
他们对此感到非常不安。

69
00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:13.636
A swarm is a congregation of tens of thousands of volunteers
集群由成千上万的志愿者组成，

70
00:04:13.660 --> 00:04:17.660
that have chosen of their own will to converge on a common goal.
他们自愿地聚焦在 一个共同的目标上。

71
00:04:18.380 --> 00:04:20.780
There's this "Futurama" quote:
“飞出个未来”里面有一句台词：

72
00:04:22.940 --> 00:04:26.700
"When push comes to shove, you gotta do what you love --
“到了紧要关头， 你必须做你喜欢做的事，

73
00:04:27.860 --> 00:04:29.436
even if it's not a good idea."
即使那不是个好主意。”

74
00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:31.276
(Laughter)
（笑声）

75
00:04:31.300 --> 00:04:33.516
I mean, seriously, what kind of idiot thinks
说真的， 什么样的蠢蛋会认为

76
00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:36.700
they can change the world by starting a political party?
他们可以通过建立一个 党派来改变世界？

77
00:04:38.686 --> 00:04:39.836
(Laughter)
（笑声）

78
00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:41.636
This kind of idiot, apparently.
我这样的蠢蛋，很明显。

79
00:04:41.660 --> 00:04:42.860
But it works!
但这竟然行得通！

80
00:04:44.660 --> 00:04:47.116
What you need to do is to put a stake in the ground.
你要做的是迈出第一步。

81
00:04:47.140 --> 00:04:49.276
You need to announce your goal.
你需要宣告你的目标。

82
00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:52.260
Just say, "I want to accomplish this."
就说，“我想要完成这个。”

83
00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:54.700
I'm going to do this.
我要去达到这个目标。

84
00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:59.060
And it doesn't need to be very costly.
这不一定会很费钱。

85
00:04:59.860 --> 00:05:03.700
My announcement was just two lines in a chat channel.
我的宣言仅仅是在一个 聊天频道里的两行话。

86
00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:09.236
"Hey, look, the Pirate Party has its website up now after New Year's."
“嘿，看，海盗党在新年后 有了自己的网站。”

87
00:05:09.260 --> 00:05:10.476
And the address.
并附上网址。

88
00:05:09.986 --> 00:05:11.706
That was all the advertising I ever did.
那是我所做的全部广告。

89
00:05:11.706 --> 00:05:16.276
The next time I had several hundred activists wanting to work with us.
一下子就有了几百名积极分子 想要和我们合作。

90
00:05:17.700 --> 00:05:20.156
When you provide such a focus point,
当你提供了一个如此有凝聚力的点，

91
00:05:20.180 --> 00:05:23.116
a swarm intelligence emerges.
集群智能就出现了。

92
00:05:23.140 --> 00:05:25.180
When people can rally to a flag.
人们可以团结在一面旗帜下。

93
00:05:26.020 --> 00:05:31.500
And that's what gives you this two orders of magnitude of cost efficiency.
这些可以为你提高两个 数级量的成本效率。

94
00:05:32.260 --> 00:05:33.956
It's a huge advantage --
这是一个巨大的优势——

95
00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:36.900
you're running circles around all the legacy organizations.
你大大超越了所有传统的组织。

96
00:05:38.980 --> 00:05:43.276
And there are four goals that need to be fulfilled in your goal
你的目标需要实现四项标准，

97
00:05:42.420 --> 00:05:44.586
in order for this to work.
它才可以实现。

98
00:05:46.260 --> 00:05:50.596
These four criteria are that your goal must be:
你的目标必须要符合这四个标准：

99
00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:55.620
tangible, credible, inclusive and epic.
切实，可信， 包容，以及伟大。

100
00:05:57.020 --> 00:05:59.420
Let's take a look at them: It needs to be tangible.
让我们看看这些： 你的目标必须是切实的。

101
00:06:00.020 --> 00:06:01.236
A lot of people say,
有许多人说，

102
00:06:00.784 --> 00:06:03.280
"Well, you know, we should make the world a better place,"
“我们应该把世界变得更好。”

103
00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:07.306
or, "Yeah, we should all feel good now."
或者，“我们现在应该感觉很好。”

104
00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:10.380
Not going to work.
这些不可行。

105
00:06:11.260 --> 00:06:12.820
You need a binary.
你需要有分明的调理。

106
00:06:13.500 --> 00:06:16.156
Are we there yet, or are we not there yet?
我们成功了? 还是没有达成目标？

107
00:06:16.180 --> 00:06:17.436
It needs to be credible.
你的目标必须是可信的。

108
00:06:17.460 --> 00:06:20.716
Somebody seeing the project plan that you're posting needs to see
你发出的项目计划 需要让人看到

109
00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:22.836
that, yes, this project plan will take us
它可以把我们

110
00:06:22.860 --> 00:06:25.036
from where we are to where we want to be.
从原地带引到 我们想达到的地方。

111
00:06:24.946 --> 00:06:27.506
You need to break it down into subgoals
你必须把你的目标切分成

112
00:06:27.380 --> 00:06:30.276
that each by themselves are seen as doable,
可付诸实践的子目标，

113
00:06:30.300 --> 00:06:32.716
and when you add the subgoals together,
当达成了所有子目标时，

114
00:06:32.740 --> 00:06:35.236
we've gone to where we want.
我们就到了我们想去的地方。

115
00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:36.476
It needs to be --
它必须——

116
00:06:36.500 --> 00:06:39.916
and this is where it gets exciting in terms of working swarmwise --
这就是集群智能让人兴奋的地方——

117
00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:41.796
it needs to be inclusive.
它必须是包容的。

118
00:06:41.820 --> 00:06:45.476
Anybody who sees this project plan needs to immediately say,
任何看到项目计划的人会立刻说，

119
00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:48.820
"I want to do this -- and there's my spot!"
“我想要做这个，那是我的位置！”

120
00:06:50.180 --> 00:06:53.676
And they will be able to jump right into the project
他们能够立马付诸实践

121
00:06:53.700 --> 00:06:59.076
and start working on it without asking anybody's permission.
并在无需任何人许可的 情况下开始实施计划。

122
00:06:59.100 --> 00:07:01.180
And that is exactly what'll happen.
那正是将要发生的。

123
00:07:02.580 --> 00:07:06.020
And, last but not least, it needs to be epic.
最后，你的目标必须是伟大的。

124
00:07:07.260 --> 00:07:11.556
It needs to energize people. It needs to electrify people.
它必须使人感到激情。 它必须令人迸出火花。

125
00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:12.980
Shoot for the moon!
向月球出发！

126
00:07:14.660 --> 00:07:16.756
On second thought, don't shoot for the moon,
现在想想，不要向月球出发，

127
00:07:16.780 --> 00:07:19.356
we've already been there -- shoot for Mars!
我们已经到过那个地方了—— 向火星出发！

128
00:07:18.970 --> 00:07:20.896
(Laughter)
（笑声）

129
00:07:23.380 --> 00:07:24.916
In contrast,
与此相反，

130
00:07:24.940 --> 00:07:29.956
you will never be able to get a volunteer swarm forming
一个志愿集群永远不会聚集

131
00:07:29.980 --> 00:07:34.660
around making the most correct tax audit ever.
去完成最正确的税务审计。

132
00:07:37.020 --> 00:07:39.820
Doesn't electrify people. Go to Mars.
它不会使人迸出火花的， 向火星出发！

133
00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:44.396
A lot of people kind of balk at the obstacles.
很多人在障碍面前会望而却步。

134
00:07:44.420 --> 00:07:46.876
We're going to climb a huge mountain.
我们要去攀爬一个巨大的山峰。

135
00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:49.116
So how do you motivate people to do that?
那么，你如何鼓舞人们？

136
00:07:49.140 --> 00:07:52.100
Well, it turns out that obstacles are not the problem.
结果证明，障碍不是问题。

137
00:07:52.900 --> 00:07:55.756
Not knowing the obstacles is the problem.
不知道障碍才是问题。

138
00:07:55.780 --> 00:07:57.596
If you know how high the mountain is,
如果你知道山有多高，

139
00:07:57.620 --> 00:08:00.156
you know exactly what it takes to scale it.
你知道去测量它需要什么。

140
00:08:00.180 --> 00:08:03.820
We know exactly how far away Mars is and what it takes to get there.
我们确切地知道火星有多远 以及如何去那里。

141
00:08:04.420 --> 00:08:06.460
If you can plan it like a project,
如果你像一个项目一样去规划它，

142
00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:09.556
you can plan what resources you need
你可以计划你需要的资源，

143
00:08:09.580 --> 00:08:12.436
and you can execute it, exactly like a project.
你就可以执行它，就像执行项目一样。

144
00:08:12.460 --> 00:08:13.996
Let's see: we're going to Mars,
让我们看看：我们要去火星，

145
00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:17.156
we need two dozen volunteer rocket scientists,
我们需要24个火箭科学家志愿者，

146
00:08:17.180 --> 00:08:20.116
one dozen volunteer metallurgists,
12个冶金学家志愿者，

147
00:08:20.140 --> 00:08:24.676
some crazy dude who will mix rocket fuel in his backyard
还有些能在自家的后院 混合火箭燃料的疯子，

148
00:08:24.700 --> 00:08:25.900
and so on.
以及诸如此类。

149
00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:30.676
When you can list the resources, you know what you need to get there.
当你能列出资源清单， 你知道到达那你需要什么。

150
00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:33.620
When you know what you need to get there, you can go there.
当你知道需要什么才能到达那， 你就可以去那。

151
00:08:35.926 --> 00:08:41.790
And the next thing is to encourage this development of a swarm intelligence,
然后下一个事情是鼓励 这个集群智慧的发展，

152
00:08:42.500 --> 00:08:44.780
which is where the cost efficiency comes in.
这正是成本效率显现的地方。

153
00:08:45.940 --> 00:08:52.260
There's a TED Talk on motivation that debunks that we work for money,
有一个TED的演讲 打破了我们为钱工作这一谎言，

154
00:08:53.619 --> 00:08:59.436
and it presents science on how we're really motivated by three things,
它用科学证明了 当我们面对大型的创意性工作时，

155
00:08:59.460 --> 00:09:01.116
in terms of larger creative tasks,
当我们投身于比自己更大的号召时，

156
00:09:00.926 --> 00:09:03.916
when we work for something bigger than ourselves.
我们会被三个因素激励。

157
00:09:04.140 --> 00:09:08.140
We work for autonomy, mastery and purpose.
我们为自主权，掌控，和意义工作。

158
00:09:09.940 --> 00:09:11.956
We've covered purpose already.
我们已经讲过意义了。

159
00:09:11.980 --> 00:09:17.060
As in, working for something bigger, tangible, credible, inclusive and epic.
就是为一些更远大的，切实的 可信的，包容的和伟大的事情工作。

160
00:09:17.936 --> 00:09:22.560
So, where that motivation talk ends,
那个 TED 演讲结束时，

161
00:09:22.300 --> 00:09:25.716
what it doesn't answer is,
它没有回答的是，

162
00:09:25.740 --> 00:09:30.620
how do you build an organization that harnesses this motivational power.
你如何利用这种激励力量 来建立一个组织。

163
00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:33.996
